		title		: "Lesson 7: What Are You Doing?",
		text		: "1\n00:00:19,545 --> 00:00:20,927\nHello, everyone.\n\n2\n00:00:20,827 --> 00:00:22,609\nToday I satart my new job.\n\n3\n00:00:23,309 --> 00:00:24,191\nAwesome!\n\n4\n00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:27,629\nI meet my new boss and my co-workers.\n\n5\n00:00:27,717 --> 00:00:31,776\nI am excited but nervous.\n\n6\n00:00:32,363 --> 00:00:34,780\nHere I go!\n\n7\n00:00:48,068 --> 00:00:51,968\nCome in.\n\n8\n00:00:53,036 --> 00:00:56,466\nWell, Anna, welcome.\n\n9\n00:00:56,575 --> 00:00:58,083\nThank you.\n\n10\n00:00:58,183 --> 00:01:00,900\nI am your boss, Caty Weaver.\n\n11\n00:01:01,001 --> 00:01:03,418\nBut, please call me Caty.\n\n12\n00:01:03,519 --> 00:01:04,625\nThank you, Ms. Weaver.\n\n13\n00:01:04,725 --> 00:01:06,838\nJust Caty.\n\n14\n00:01:06,838 --> 00:01:08,852\nSure thing, Ms. Weaver.\n\n15\n00:01:08,952 --> 00:01:12,384\nOkay then. Are you excited?\n\n16\n00:01:12,488 --> 00:01:15,006\nYes, I am excited!\n\n17\n00:01:15,106 --> 00:01:18,426\nSo sorry, but I am busy.\n\n18\n00:01:18,530 --> 00:01:20,845\nPlease meet your co-workers.\n\n19\n00:01:20,948 --> 00:01:25,076\nBut remember, they are busy working.\n\n20\n00:01:25,177 --> 00:01:27,594\nSure. Thanks, Ms. Weaver.\n\n21\n00:01:34,859 --> 00:01:37,676\nHi there! I’m Anna.\n\n22\n00:01:37,779 --> 00:01:39,895\nHi, Anna. I’m Anne.\n\n23\n00:01:39,996 --> 00:01:42,111\nNice to meet you.\n\n24\n00:01:41,043 --> 00:01:42,182\nWhat are you doing?\n\n25\n00:01:42,283 --> 00:01:43,490\nUm, I’m writing.\n\n26\n00:01:43,594 --> 00:01:45,530\nYou are writing!\n\n27\n00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:47,350\nYou are writing a lot!\n\n28\n00:01:47,451 --> 00:01:48,559\n(Spills papers) Oh! Oh dear.\n\n29\n00:01:48,676 --> 00:01:50,288\nNo! No! That's okay.\n\n30\n00:01:50,516 --> 00:01:51,623\nThat’s okay. Really.\n\n31\n00:01:51,623 --> 00:01:53,143\nI am sorry!\n\n32\n00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:55,070\nPlease. Please.\n\n33\n00:01:55,179 --> 00:01:57,206\nPlease stop. Please.\n\n34\n00:01:57,947 --> 00:02:02,077\nSorry. Sorry.\n\n35\n00:02:26,104 --> 00:02:33,652\n(in the studio) “and people all around the world are waiting to hear news about the next president…”\n\n36\n00:02:33,858 --> 00:02:35,065\nJonathan, hi! Remember me?\n\n37\n00:02:35,273 --> 00:02:36,681\nI live in your building.\n\n38\n00:02:36,983 --> 00:02:39,099\nOh. Uh. Hi, Anna.\n\n39\n00:02:39,305 --> 00:02:40,817\nWhat are you doing?\n\n40\n00:02:40,918 --> 00:02:42,829\nI am doing my show!\n\n41\n00:02:43,137 --> 00:02:46,253\nOh, sorry. Are you recording?\n\n42\n00:02:46,382 --> 00:02:50,109\nYes! And, now I have to record again!\n\n43\n00:02:50,211 --> 00:02:52,726\nSorry. Have a good show.\n\n44\n00:02:53,050 --> 00:02:54,662\nThank you.\n\n45\n00:02:54,771 --> 00:02:56,383\nSorry.\n\n46\n00:03:03,231 --> 00:03:05,951\nThe word of the day is social. Social -\n\n47\n00:03:04,991 --> 00:03:06,499\nOh! Hi!\n\n48\n00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:07,807\n- is an adjective.\n\n49\n00:03:08,013 --> 00:03:09,225\nHi! I’m Anna!\n\n50\n00:03:09,426 --> 00:03:10,532\nHi. I’m Amelia.\n\n51\n00:03:10,740 --> 00:03:11,863\nNice to meet you!\n\n52\n00:03:12,075 --> 00:03:13,684\nWhat are you doing?\n\n53\n00:03:13,784 --> 00:03:15,798\nI’m reading.\n\n54\n00:03:16,010 --> 00:03:18,529\nAre you reading the news? Hi!\n\n55\n00:03:18,489 --> 00:03:21,530\nNo, I’m reading for my show.\n\n56\n00:03:23,653 --> 00:03:25,688\n(to camera person) Can I read again?\n\n57\n00:03:26,599 --> 00:03:29,215\nSorry.\n\n58\n00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:31,754\nThis day is not going well.\n\n59\n00:03:57,386 --> 00:04:01,108\nAnna! Hi! What’re you doing?\n\n60\n00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:04,431\nI am bothering people, Ms. Weaver.\n\n61\n00:04:05,972 --> 00:04:09,398\nLet’s go to my office and talk.\n\n62\n00:04:10,314 --> 00:04:12,128\nI like to talk with you, Ms. Weaver.\n\n63\n00:04:12,846 --> 00:04:14,358\nIt’s Caty.\n\n64\n00:04:14,459 --> 00:04:15,968\nRight. Thanks ...\n\n65\n00:04:16,846 --> 00:04:18,156\nMs. Weaver",
