		title		: "Lesson 18: She Always Does That",
		text		: "1\n00:00:16,562 --> 00:00:19,378\nHello, from Washington, D.C.!\n\n2\n00:00:19,579 --> 00:00:24,111\nToday at work I am reading the news for the first time.\n\n3\n00:00:24,316 --> 00:00:26,336\nI am really nervous.\n\n4\n00:00:26,843 --> 00:00:29,963\nBut my boss, Ms. Weaver, is here to help me.\n\n5\n00:00:30,271 --> 00:00:32,489\nNow, Anna, remember.\n\n6\n00:00:32,691 --> 00:00:37,021\nWhen we read the news we are always reading facts.\n\n7\n00:00:37,222 --> 00:00:39,538\nWe never show our feelings.\n\n8\n00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:41,147\nSure thing, Ms. Weaver.\n\n9\n00:00:41,248 --> 00:00:43,060\nGreat. Are you ready?\n\n10\n00:00:45,055 --> 00:00:46,563\nYes.\n\n11\n00:00:46,764 --> 00:00:49,080\nOkay, let’s try the first story!\n\n12\n00:00:51,776 --> 00:00:55,616\nHello, and welcome to The News.\n\n13\n00:00:56,419 --> 00:01:00,662\nA new book is very popular with children and families.\n\n14\n00:01:00,964 --> 00:01:02,978\nThis is it.\n\n15\n00:01:03,983 --> 00:01:07,106\nIt is about a lost duckling.\n\n16\n00:01:07,607 --> 00:01:10,323\nThe duck's mother cannot find him.\n\n17\n00:01:10,549 --> 00:01:17,002\nStop! Anna, when you say the words “duck” and “duckling”\n\n18\n00:01:17,205 --> 00:01:19,019\nyou look really sad.\n\n19\n00:01:19,119 --> 00:01:20,429\nI do?\n\n20\n00:01:20,555 --> 00:01:23,271\nYes. Sad is a feeling.\n\n21\n00:01:23,692 --> 00:01:25,401\nSad is not a fact.\n\n22\n00:01:25,722 --> 00:01:27,840\nSorry. Let me try again.\n\n23\n00:01:28,151 --> 00:01:30,968\nOkay, she’s trying again! And go.\n\n24\n00:01:34,003 --> 00:01:37,530\nHello, and welcome to The News.\n\n25\n00:01:38,341 --> 00:01:42,785\nA new book is very popular with children and families.\n\n26\n00:01:43,006 --> 00:01:45,121\nThis is it.\n\n27\n00:01:45,937 --> 00:01:48,958\nIt is about a lost duckling.\n\n28\n00:01:49,158 --> 00:01:51,078\nThe duck’s mother can not find ‘im.\n\n29\n00:01:51,279 --> 00:01:54,095\nBut a family gives him a home.\n\n30\n00:01:54,415 --> 00:01:57,736\nStop! Anna, you are doing it again.\n\n31\n00:01:58,150 --> 00:02:01,468\nThis story is very sad.\n\n32\n00:02:02,087 --> 00:02:05,714\nI have an idea. Let’s read the second story.\n\n33\n00:02:06,038 --> 00:02:08,754\nShe’s reading the second story. And … go!\n\n34\n00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:27,851\nHello , and welcome to The News.\n\n35\n00:02:28,655 --> 00:02:35,803\nIn Indiana, a grandmother is the first 80-year-old woman to win The Race Car 500.\n\n36\n00:02:36,026 --> 00:02:38,240\nThat is awesome!\n\n37\n00:02:38,359 --> 00:02:44,602\nStop! Stop! Anna, please -- no feelings.\n\n38\n00:02:45,005 --> 00:02:50,946\nRight. But it is awesome that an 80-year-old grandmother wins a car race.\n\n39\n00:02:51,284 --> 00:02:54,000\nJust the facts, Anna.\n\n40\n00:02:54,303 --> 00:02:56,320\nRight.\n\n41\n00:02:59,371 --> 00:03:02,694\nHello, and welcome to The News.\n\n42\n00:03:02,928 --> 00:03:10,577\nIn Indiana, a grandmother is the first 80-year-old woman to win The Race Car 500.\n\n43\n00:03:10,778 --> 00:03:13,496\nShe rarely talks to reporters.\n\n44\n00:03:13,799 --> 00:03:18,832\nBut when she does, she often says, “Nothing can stop me now!”\n\n45\n00:03:19,065 --> 00:03:21,681\nI am very happy for her!\n\n46\n00:03:21,799 --> 00:03:23,127\nStop, stop, stop!!\n\n47\n00:03:23,341 --> 00:03:27,468\nAnna, you cannot say you are happy.\n\n48\n00:03:27,788 --> 00:03:29,600\nBut I am happy.\n\n49\n00:03:29,707 --> 00:03:31,114\nBut you can’t say it.\n\n50\n00:03:31,527 --> 00:03:32,334\nWhy?\n\n51\n00:03:32,456 --> 00:03:33,872\nThis is the News.\n\n52\n00:03:34,089 --> 00:03:36,909\nHappy and sad are feelings.\n\n53\n00:03:37,132 --> 00:03:39,953\nYou can’t have them in The News.\n\n54\n00:03:40,306 --> 00:03:43,323\nOkay. I got it.\n\n55\n00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:48,867\nOkay. Let’s try the third story.\n\n56\n00:03:49,171 --> 00:03:50,983\nShe’s reading the third story!\n\n57\n00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:05,367\nHello and welcome to The News.\n\n58\n00:04:05,669 --> 00:04:13,922\nCity politicians in Big Town are using city money to have a big party on a cruise ship.\n\n59\n00:04:14,230 --> 00:04:19,766\nThey are taking the money for the party from the children’s library.\n\n60\n00:04:20,171 --> 00:04:22,989\nWhat?! That makes me very angry.\n\n61\n00:04:22,989 --> 00:04:24,307\nNo, no, no!\n\n62\n00:04:24,407 --> 00:04:27,428\nAnna, you cannot say you are angry!\n\n63\n00:04:27,652 --> 00:04:29,568\nThis is The News!!!\n\n64\n00:04:29,772 --> 00:04:31,194\nWhat can I do, Ms. Weaver?\n\n65\n00:04:31,303 --> 00:04:36,239\nTake out my feelings and put them here … on the news desk?\n\n66\n00:04:36,339 --> 00:04:41,185\nYes. Yes. That’s right! Now you’ve got it!\n\n67\n00:04:41,185 --> 00:04:43,238\nLet’s repeat the first story.\n\n68\n00:04:43,345 --> 00:04:47,370\nThis is going to be a very long day.\n\n69\n00:04:47,997 --> 00:04:49,407\nUntil next time!\n\n70\n00:04:51,703 --> 00:04:55,057\nHello, and welcome to The News.",
